{
  "texts": [
    "For example, Sharchilev et al.'s (2018) leafinfluence method adapts influence functions to gradient boosted decision tree ensembles.",
    "By assuming a fixed tree structure and then focusing only on the trees' leaves, leafinfluence's tree-based estimates are significantly faster than influence functions on deep models (Brophy et al., 2023).",
    "Group influence functions A major strength of influence functions is that it is one of the few influence analysis methods that has been studied beyond the pointwise domain.",
    "For example, Koh et al.'s (2019) follow-on paper analyzes influence functions' empirical performance estimating group influence.",
    "In particular, Koh et al. (2019) consider coherent training data subpopulations whose removal is expected to have a large, broad effect on the model."
  ]
}